{
  "stem": "19690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 75.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And then after a few days, they were moved further into Germany, further into the central part of Germany, where essentially, a lot of them remained the rest of their lives.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "They never went back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "Later that day, Hitler made his famous speech that he had decided to invade Poland because of the Danzig perimeter, which was a road through Poland to get to Danzig, which was a German city.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And he wanted the Danzig free, and as a result, he justified going into Poland and attacking Poland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "He didn't care whether the English would do anything or the French would do anything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "They can do anything they wanted.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We essentially remained where we were.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Restrictions became very difficult to live with.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For instance, you could not use a radio with anything but German stations.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They would have sound trucks going down the streets which were essentially direction-finding equipment and they would monitor what radios were being listened to.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if you were listening to a foreign station, they would pick it up, come to the house, take your radio away.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Also, they came and they confiscated all the silver, all the gold, all the valuables in the house.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was already between November '38 and September '39.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we could no longer travel without a permit.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "All of our passports were taken away if we had them, and my mother had one because we were in Switzerland the year before.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "All the passports were confiscated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You couldn't travel.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You-- the men could no longer go by car to Mannheim, they had to go by train.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They had to get a permit to go there every day and learn their barbering.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
